post_text:
***Update: As a result of Governor Kelly's announcement to delay the start of school, this timeline will now need to be modified***

The USD 402 Safe Return Task Force is working on plans for Augusta's return to school. It is important that the district share information, when available, on the process to better prepare and inform our community.

Below you will find a tentative timeline. This is the timeline that the task force and oversight groups will be operating under. With that said, it is important to understand that due to an ever changing environment, this timeline may be subject to change.

The district will continue to communicate as more information becomes available. Thank you for your support as we navigate through this challenging, ever-changing, environment.

We have received a number of positive, supportive, and encouraging messages from staff and parents. Your support means a lot to us.

Preschool, Kindergarten and New Students to Augusta USD 402 are asked to fill out the New Student information so that when Online Enrollment opens up July 27th, you will be ready! https://registration.powerschool.com/family/gosnap.aspx?action=20752&culture=en&TriggerAutoLogOut=15

Preschool: Augusta offers a couple different options for Preschool. At-Risk and Paid Full Day Preschool. If you have questions about the different programs you can visit our website or contact Kristie Thackery at kthackery@usd402.com.

Kindergarten: A child who is five (5) years of age on or before August 31, 2020 is eligible to enroll for Kindergarten.

A copy of your child's state official birth certificate and immunization records is required to attend school.

post_text:
During these last weeks, our entire staff has worked hard to care for kids and help them feel connected. We are grateful for your positive attitudes, the extra time spent learning new ways to teach and communicate, taking on new or different roles, and the additional planning it took to completely re-invent our education process with little time or notice. We appreciate each of you and your commitment to our students. Thank you!

There's one group we especially want to recognize now - those staff members who are retiring. It's not the celebration they deserve but we have made a video featuring each of our 2019-2020 retirees. We hope you'll join us in thanking them for their service and wishing them well.
https://youtu.be/UFZ1Ta41Pq4

#AugustaProud

Augusta Schools USD 402
April 21 at 3:15 PM ·

The schools in Augusta are partnering with the Augusta Public Library to collect any library books that have not been returned. If you still have any library books at home, please return them to the outside book drop at the Augusta Public Library, 1609 State Street . They have graciously agreed to collect, sort, and return our school library books so you will not have to keep them over the summer. shared_text:
Kansas State Department of Education
March 17 at 9:01 AM ·

The Continuous Learning Task Force worked throughout the night on a comprehensive plan for delivering education to students while school buildings remain closed. The task force anticipates having a draft of this plan finalized by the end of the day Wednesday, March 18.

We can’t emphasize enough that this is a herculean effort being led by our Kansas teachers. We thank this group - and every teacher in Kansas - for all they’re doing to ensure that learning continues for our students.

Please lend them your support, and trust that they are working to provide the very best opportunities for our students during this time of uncertainty.

EDIT March 17 4:25 p.m. - The list of educators on the Continuous Learning Task Force is available here: https://www.ksde.org/Home/Quick-Links/News-Room/commissioner-watson-convenes-continuous-learning-task-force-1

#YouthArtMonth #KSArtEd

Nurse Tonya and SRO Meckel presented Booster to Belts to K-3rd grade at Augusta Schools USD 402 - Garfield Elementary. It stressed the importance of seat belt safety, especially with booster seats, and that you should always wear them properly whenever traveling in a vehicle.

If you are unsure what seat your child should be using - The National Highway Traffic Safety Administration has a tool you can enter age, height and weight and will tell you which they should be using based on this information. https://www.nhtsa.gov/campaign/right-seat

Butler County residents interested in having a child safety seat inspected must schedule an appointment for this service by contacting the Butler County Sheriff’s Office at 316-320-1294.
#boostertobelt #seatbeltsareforeveryone #carseatsafety Augusta Department Of Public Safety

post_text: Kansas law KSA 8-1556 requires all motorists to stop when approaching or overtaking a stopped school bus displaying its flashing red lights and stop arm. Motorists are to remains stopped until the bus is no longer displaying its flashing red lights and stop arm. Violation of this law not only endangers children but is punishable by a fine and court costs in excess of $420. #stoponredkidsahead

Ms. Moore's Kindergarten class at Augusta Schools USD 402 - Lincoln Elementary learned how to be germ busters today. They were given some germ lotion, looked at it under a black-light, washed their hand and then looked under the black light again to see where they could improve washing their hands.

The best and most efficient way to be a germ buster is to wash your hands properly. Scrubbing in between your fingers and your fingernails very good while you sing your ABCs or counting to 20 is a great way to keep from sick! 😷 Don't worry parent's - you kids will be well by the end of the day.

post_text: The 2019 Augustan Yearbook was honored with the Kansas Scholastic Press Association (KSPA) All-Kansas Award. This award is the top award the association gives, which means the Augustan is one of the best yearbooks in the state. Yearbooks are judged on five categories: theme, coverage, reporting, photography, and design. The Augustan earned All-Kansas ratings in all five categories. The Augustan staff will be recognized with a plaque at the KSPA State Contest opening ceremony May 2, 2020 at the Memorial Union at the University of Kansas. Way to go! #augustaproud
